 The Federal Road Safety Corps in Bauchi State has confirmed that three members of vigilante lost their lives in a lone auto crash in the state. The Sector Commander of FRSC in the state, Yusuf Abdullahi, who disclosed this on Sunday in Bauchi, said that seven others sustained varying degrees of injuries. Abdullahi said that the accident occurred at Zadawa village, along Misau-Azare Road, around 10:30am, on Saturday. The Sector Commander stated that it took the personnel of the Corps about 15 minutes to arrive at the scene to clear the site, blaming the accident on wrongful overtaking. “The accident involved 10 members of the vigilante while travelling to Azare, headquarters of Katagum Local Government Area, to attend the wedding of the daughter of Minister for Education, Mallam Adamu Adamu. “Three male adults lost their lives while seven others sustained injuries. However, they were not in the governor’s motorcade. “They went earlier before the governor and you know, whenever there is a function, they always go to assist in maintaining law and order. “One person died on the spot while two others passed later at the Federal Medical Center, Azare,” he said. According to him, those injured are currently receiving treatment at the hospital, while the corpses of the dead were deposited at the morgue. Meanwhile, one person reportedly lost his life in a separate road accident, on Saturday, around Ramadan Press, along the Bypass road within the Bauchi metropolis. Abdullahi said that the accident occurred when a Sharon bus tried to avoid colliding with a Honda Civic car. He said that the bus skidded and crashed, adding that “The Motor Transport Department of the Police Command conducted the exercise,” he said. (NAN). 